<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-10T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-10T07:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 165.102/511</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-10T13:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1915, 1 p.m</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 11, 3.30
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2199. Department’s 1629, 5th. Foreign Office inquires preliminarily
                                whether <hi rend="italic">Neches</hi> brings cargo destined for
                                Germany, what such cargo is composed of, and whether its
                                transshipment through Holland is guaranteed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>